name: Merle Thornton
summary: Merle Thornton, a prominent Queensland feminist activist, author, and academic, passed away at the age of 93. She made history in 1965 when she shackled herself to a bar in Brisbane to protest against the discriminatory laws that prohibited women from drinking in public bars. Her courageous action garnered global attention and contributed to overturning these laws. As a tribute to her legacy, the Queensland government has announced plans to erect a statue in her honor.

name: Jetstar
summary: Jetstar, an Australian low-cost airline, is facing legal challenges and incidents. A class action lawsuit has been filed against the airline for allegedly failing to refund passengers for canceled flights during the COVID-19 pandemic. Meanwhile, Jetstar Asia has launched a new service from Singapore to Colombo. In a bizarre incident, a man was arrested after opening an emergency exit door and walking on the wing of a Jetstar plane at an Australian airport before climbing down on the tarmac. The airline has also launched a mega sale with airfares as low as $34. In other news, Jetstar is facing a class action lawsuit over canceled flights during COVID-19, while a survivor of a rare 1964 Oldsmobile Jetstar 88 has been discovered with a unique powertrain.
